ter's%20questions%20on%20allegations%20of%20an%20Australian%20journalist's%20claims%20not%20allowed%20to%20cover%20Indian%20general%20elections%20and%20said%20that%20the%20country%20determines%20which%20non-citizens%20it%20allows%20to%20enter%2C%20either%20as%20short-term%20travellers%20or%20international%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20a%20question%20by%20a%20Pakistani%20reporter%20on%20allegations%20of%20denial%20of%20visa%20renewal%20to%20Australian%20journalist%2C%20Avani%20Dias%2C%20US%20State%20Department%20Principal%20Deputy%20Spokesperson%20Vedant%20Patel%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Government%20of%20India%20can%20speak%20to%20its%20own%20visa%20policy.%20That's%20not%20something%20I'm%20going%20to%20opine%20on%20from%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPatel%20further%20emphasised%20the%20role%20of%20the%20free%20press%20in%20the%20fabric%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBroadly%2C%20we%20have%20been%20clear%20with%20countries%20around%20the%20world%20about%20the%20integral%20role%20that%20a%20free%20press%20plays%20in%20the%20fabric%20of%20democracy.%20That's%20why%20we%20come%20up%20here%20and%20take%20questions%20regularly.%20But%20I%20will%20let%20the%20officials%20in%20India%20speak%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAvani%20Dias%2C%20an%20Australian%20journalist%2C%20claimed%20that%20she%20was%20not%20allowed%20to%20cover%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20and%20was%20compelled%20to%20leave%20the%20country.%20However%2C%20the%20sources%20highlighted%20that%20her%20claims%20are%20%26quot%3Bnot%20correct%2C%20misleading%20and%20mischievous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20sources%20said%20that%20Avani%20Dias%2C%20South%20Asia%20Correspondent%20of%20Australian%20Broadcasting%20Corporation%20(ABC)%20was%20also%20found%20to%20have%20violated%20visa%20rules%20while%20undertaking%20her%20professional%20pursuits%20while%20%26quot%3Bundertaking%20her%20professional%20pursuits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5C