i%3EBe%20realistic%20about%20your%20spending%2C%20and%20consider%20multiple%20income%20streams.%C2%A0%5Cn%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20common%20theme%20that%20I%20have%20been%20noticing%20with%20my%20clients%20lately%20is%20the%20desire%20to%20retire%20early.%20Many%20people%20are%20considering%20an%20early%20or%20partial%20retirement%20for%20more%20fulfilling%20roles.%20However%2C%20the%20reality%20of%20leaving%20work%20early%20can%20be%20far%20different%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20retirement%20is%20not%20for%20everyone.%20According%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebri.org%2Fdocs%2Fdefault-source%2Frcs%2F2020-rcs%2Frcs_20-fs-2.pdf%5C%22%3EEmployee%20Benefit%20Research%20Institute%20(EBRI)%3C%2Fa%3E%202020%20survey%2C%20only%2011%25%20of%20today's%20workers%20plan%20to%20retire%20before%20age%2060.%20If%20you%20fall%20within%20the%2011%25%20crowd%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20things%20you%20need%20to%20consider%20before%20deciding%20on%20early%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Figure%20out%20what%20you%20want%20to%20do%20with%20your%20time%20during%20retirement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20our%20working%20years%2C%20we%20typically%20have%20many%20activities%20happening%20throughout%20the%20day%20to%20keep%20us%20occupied.%20Whether%20you%20are%20passionate%20about%20various%20hobbies%2C%20volunteering%20your%20time%2C%20or%20traveling%20the%20world%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20that%20you%20figure%20out%20how%20you%20want%20to%20spend%20your%20time%20during%20retirement.%20Many%20people%20believe%20that%20they%20will%20be%20able%20to%20easily%20fill%20their%20time%2C%20only%20to%20find%20themselves%20bored%20during%20their%20transition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20is%20the%20time%20to%20partake%20in%20all%20the%20things%20that%20you%20may%20have%20put%20off%20for%20years.%20Make%20sure%20that%20you%20come%20up%20with%20a%20plan%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffinancial-independence-retire-early%5C%22%3Eearly%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Know%20that%20there%20may%20be%20a%20lack%20of%20human%20and%20social%20connection%20due%20to%20your%20peers%20still%20working%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20traditional%20retirement%2C%20many%20of%20your%20peers%20and%20friends%20will%20also%20be%20retired%20or%20nearing%20retirement.%20Therefore%2C%20you%20could%20have%20endless%20dinner%20parties%2C%20brunch%20dates%2C%20and%20time%20with%20the%20people%20you%20love%20and%20care%20about%20the%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20early%20retirement%2C%20many%20individuals%20start%20to%20experience%20a%20lack%20of%20social%20interaction%20since%20their%20peers%20are%20all%20likely%20still%20working.%20While%20you%20may%20have%20time%20to%20play%20golf%20or%20go%20to%20the%20beach%20during%20the%20day%2C%20your%20friends%20who%20are%20working%209-to-5%20don't%20have%20that%20luxury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20I%20have%20seen%20clients%20opt%20for%20partial%20retirement%20and%20work%20part-time%20just%20so%20that%20they%20can%20continue%20to%20engage%20with%20their%20peers.%20If%20you%20do%20not%20have%20a%20big%20family%2C%20grandkids%2C%20or%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20new%20friends%20to%20occupy%20your%20time%2C%20this%20is%20something%20to%20consider%20before%20retiring%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Be%20realistic%20about%20your%20monthly%20retirement%20income%20needs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20approach%20early%20retirement%20the%20same%20as%20traditional%20retirement%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebudget%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20you%20will%20spend%20more%20money%20than%20you%20think%20during%20early%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20years%20of%20retirement%2C%20when%20you%20are%20younger%2C%20healthier%2C%20and%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20free%20time%2C%20you%20may%20find%20yourself%20spending%20more%20than%20you%20did%20before%20retirement.%20It%20is%20common%20for%20new%20early%20retirees%20to%20splurge%20on%20travel%2C%20home%20renovations%2C%20relocations%2C%20and%20other%20retirement%20activities.%20With%20no%20work%20to%20do%2C%20you%20are%20constantly%20seeking%20new%20activities%20to%20partake%20in%2C%20which%20usually%20have%20a%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20other%20expenses%20that%20you%20may%20have%20compared%20to%20traditional%20retirement%20are%20mortgage%20payments%2C%20childcare%20expenses%2C%20and%20debt%20payments.%20To%20prepare%20for%20all%20these%20expenses%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20create%20a%20budget%20and%20structure%20where%20you%20pay%20yourself%20on%20a%20set%20frequency%2C%20like%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Plan%20for%20unexpected%20medical%20expenses%20or%20future%20needs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMedical%20expenses%20will%20undoubtedly%20be%20one%20of%20your%20largest%20expenses%20during%20retirement.%20While%20it%20is%20nearly%20impossible%20to%20plan%20for%20exact%20medical%20expenses%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20have%20a%20big%20cash%20cushion%20set%20aside%20for%20these%20needs.%20When%20analyzing%20how%20much%20of%20a%20cushion%20to%20set%20aside%2C%20consider%20factors%20such%20as%20where%20you%20plan%20to%20retire%2C%20how%20healthy%20you%20are%2C%20and%20your%20estimated%20life%20expectancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20Medicare%20doesn't%20start%20until%20age%2065.%20This%20means%20that%20you%20will%20most%20likely%20have%20to%20apply%20for%20private%20health%20insurance%20until%20then.%20Private%20health%20insurance%20can%20be%20costly%2C%20as%20you%20do%20not%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20your%20employer%20covering%20some%20of%20the%20cost.%20It%20is%20essential%20that%20you%20consider%20this%20expense%20before%20retiring%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20factor%20to%20consider%20is%20that%20healthcare%20costs%20increase%20annually%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-causes-inflation%5C%22%3Einflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20factors.%20To%20plan%20for%20these%20expenses%2C%20you%20should%20consider%20at%20least%20a%204%25%20to%205%25%20annual%20increase%20for%20out-of-pocket%20healthcare%20expenses%20during%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Create%20passive%20income%20to%20help%20make%20your%20money%20last%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20improved%20healthcare%20and%20technology%2C%20many%20people%20are%20living%20much%20longer.%20The%20greatest%20risk%20to%20a%20successful%20retirement%20is%20that%20your%20money%20will%20run%20out%20at%20some%20point.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnchs%2Ffastats%2Flife-expectancy.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20life%20expectancy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20is%2076.4.%20Let's%20say%20you%20decided%20to%20retire%20at%20age%2040.%20You%20would%20have%20to%20make%20your%20savings%20last%20for%2036.4%20years%2C%20on%20average%2C%20compared%20to%2011.4%20years%20if%20you%20retire%20at%20age%2065.%20This%20means%20that%20your%20savings%20would%20have%20to%20last%20much%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20not%20sure%20whether%20you%20will%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20sustain%20your%20needs%20throughout%20retirement%2C%20it%20may%20be%20beneficial%20to%20consider%20creating%20some%20passive%20income%20streams%20during%20your%20early%20retirement%20years.%20Whether%20you%20plan%20to%20invest%20your%20money%20in%20long-term%20funds%20that%20pay%20dividends%20or%20have%20a%20rental%20property%20that%20generates%20positive%20cash%20flow%2C%20you%20will%20not%20regret%20having%20an%20additional%20stream%20of%20income%20during%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbu