E%20that%20would%20shield%20him%20from%20Justice%20Department%20Special%20Counsel%20Jack%20Smith's%20indictment%20over%20his%20attempts%20to%20overturn%20the%20results%20of%20the%202020%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Trump%20were%20to%20pardon%20himself%2C%20he%20would%20be%20able%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20case%2C%20as%20well%20as%20another%20case%20brought%20by%20Smith%2C%20over%20his%20hoarding%20of%20classified%20documents%20at%20Mar-a-Lago%20after%20leaving%20the%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGorsuch%2C%20himself%20a%20Trump%20appointee%2C%20entertained%20hypothetical%20questions%20about%20what%20presidents%20might%20do%20if%20they%20had%20to%20live%20with%20the%20constant%20worry%20that%20their%20successors%20would%20pursue%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them.%20He%20asked%20whether%20the%20dynamic%20would%20be%20an%20incentive%20for%20presidents%20%26quot%3Bto%20try%20to%20pardon%20themselves%26quot%3B%20before%20leaving%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPerhaps%2C%20if%20he%20feels%20he%20has%20to%2C%20he'll%20pardon%20himself%20every%20four%20years%20from%20now%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Gorsuch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGorsuch%20appeared%20cautious%20about%20tackling%20the%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20never%20answered%20whether%20a%20president%20can%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Gorsuch%20said.%20%26quot%3BHappily%2C%20it's%20never%20been%20presented%20to%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlito%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20seemed%20eager%20to%20dig%20into%20the%20subject.%20He%20told%20Michael%20Dreeben%2C%20the%20lawyer%20representing%20Smith's%20team%2C%20that%20the%20question%20might%20be%20crucial%20as%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20deliberates%20the%20scope%20of%20presidential%20immunity.%20If%20the%20court%20decides%20former%20presidents%20could%20be%20prosecuted%2C%20then%20the%20obvious%20next%20step%20would%20be%20that%20they'd%20all%20try%20to%20pardon%20themselves%2C%20Alito%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20you%20think%20we%20need%20to%20know%20at%20least%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20position%20on%20that%20issue%20in%20order%20to%20decide%20this%20case%3F%26quot%3B%20Alito%20asked.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20if%20a%20president%20has%20the%20authority%20to%20pardon%20himself%20before%20leaving%20office%2C%20and%20the%20DC%20Circuit%20is%20right%20that%20there%20is%20no%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%2C%20won't%20the%20predictable%20result%20be%20that%20presidents%20on%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20days%20of%20office%20are%20going%20to%20pardon%20themselves%20from%20anything%20that%20they%20might%20have%20been%20conceivably%20charged%20with%20committing%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDreeben%20referred%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Folc%2Fopinion%2Fpresidential-or-legislative-pardon-president%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%201974%20memorandum%20from%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20Office%20of%20Legal%20Counsel%3C%2Fa%3E%20deeming%20%26quot%3Bthat%20there%20is%20no%20self-pardon%20authority%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20noting%20the%20courts%20haven't%20decided%20the%20issue.%20But%2C%20he%20said%2C%20self-pardoning%20would%20%26quot%3Bcontradict%20a%20bedrock%20principle%20of%20our%20law%20that%20no%20person%20shall%20be%20the%20judge%20in%20their%20own%20case%26quot%3B%20and%20come%20with%20%26quot%3Bpolitical%20consequences%2C%26quot%3B%20like%20the%20political%20fallout%20former%20President%20Gerald%20Ford%20experienced%20after%20giving%20Richard%20Nixon%20a%20blanket%20pardon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20are%20adequate%20deterrents%2C%20I%20think%2C%20so%20that%20this%20kind%20of%20dystopian%20regime%20is%20not%20going%20to%20evolve%2C%26quot%3B%20Dreeben%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Trump%20wins%20the%202024%20election%20over%20President%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20he%20could%20find%20other%20ways%20to%20scuttle%20the%20two%20Justice%20Department%20indictments%20against%20him%20without%20necessarily%20pardoning%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20th