0was%20the%20Goan%20%3Cem%3Ecaril%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20was%20the%20origin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20with%20numerous%20takes%20on%20the%20dish%2C%20the%20curry%20is%20the%20heart%20and%20soul%20of%20India%2C%20so%20here%E2%80%99s%20exploring%20its%20many%20forms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E1.%20Gushtaba%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FDtRAeN_21ZQ%3Fsi%3DZ2ZofFKWlEl0lQUM%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dish%20is%20a%20spicy%20take%20on%20a%20meatball%20curry.%20Flavourful%20mutton%20mince%20balls%20are%20married%20with%20a%20thick%20yoghurt%20gravy%20to%20result%20in%20this%20preparation%20that%20is%20hailed%20as%C2%A0%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Emaharajaon%20ka%20khana%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98%20(a%20feast%20for%20kings).%20In%20fact%2C%20in%20a%20traditional%20%3Cem%3EKashmiri%20Wazwan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20feast%20comprising%2036%20dishes)%2C%20%3Cem%3Egushtaba%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20served%20as%20the%20last%20dish%20before%20dessert.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20Pulissery%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FfAtNuppiof0%3Fsi%3Di7_Jal3Z7DIBEFP3%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPopular%20in%20Kerala%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20South%20India%2C%20the%3Cem%3E%20pulissery%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20traditional%20yoghurt-based%20curry%20that%20often%20features%20pineapple%20as%20the%20hero%20ingredient.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F337104%2Feasy-recipe-for-gajar-ka-halwa-history-winter-dessert%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elip-smacking%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20has%20a%20spot%20on%20the%20Onam%20%3Cem%3Esaadya%3C%2Fem%3E%20platter.%20The%20best%20part%20of%20this%20dish%20is%20that%20you%20can%20prepare%20it%20with%20a%20seasonal%20fruit%20or%20any%20vegetable%20of%20your%20choice.%20This%20summer%2C%20why%20not%20try%20it%20with%20mango%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E3.%20Besara%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FSZNXB8a-FEU%3Fsi%3DYWRcP3-UnYPdsRTZ%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20traditional%20flavourful%20gravy%20made%20with%20ground%20mustard%20seeds%2C%20%3Cem%3Ebesara%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20famous%20not%20just%20for%20its%20delectable%20taste%20but%20also%20for%20its%20religious%20significance.%20The%20dish%20is%20one%20of%20the%2056%20that%20are%20offered%20as%20%3Cem%3Emahaprasad%3C%2Fem%3E%20at%20the%20Puri%20Shree%20Jagannath%20Temple.%20There%20are%20numerous%20variations%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebesara%3C%2Fem%3E%20depending%20on%20the%20hero%20ingredient.%20For%20instance%2C%20%3Cem%3Emaccha%20besara%3C%2Fem%3E%20refers%20to%20fish%20in%20mustard%20gravy%20while%20the%20%3Cem%3Epoi%20chingudi%20besara%3C%2Fem%3E%20features%20shrimp%20and%20spinach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E4.%20Lal%20Maas%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fx6VBBUDXQbo%3Fsi%3DgPOPnmiShzFM7zTC%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20popular%20delicacy%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20%3Cem%3Elal%20maas%3C%2Fem%3E%20literally%20translates%20to%20%E2%80%98red%20meat%E2%80%99%20and%20dates%20back%20to%20the%207th%20century.%20Legend%20says%20that%20the%20recipe%20for%20%3Cem%3Elal%20maas%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20invented%20on%20the%20go%20during%20hunting%20expeditions.%20Meat%20would%20be%20cooked%20with%20generous%20servings%20of%20yoghurt%20and%20%3Cem%3Eghee%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20the%20story%20goes%20that%20one%20Maharaja%20rejected%20the%20dish%20as%20it%20still%20gave%20off%20a%20strong%20smell%20even%20after%20cooking.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F331992%2Fmaa-kali-rabri-bhandar-avijit-patra-pannalal-kolkata-rabri-gi-tag-origin-story%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20cook%E2%80%99s%20quick%20thinking%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20adding%20chillies%20to%20the%20dish%20to%20take%20away%20the%20odour%20gave%20birth%20to%20our%20beloved%20%3Cem%3Elal%20maas%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20Masor%20Tenga%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F12E7H_wk7r8%3Fsi%3D2Lu9ggGHl05KV_MW%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quintessential%20Assamese%20dish%20translates%20to%20a%20tangy%20fish%20curry%20and%20takes%20no%20more%20than%2020%20minutes%20to%20prepare.%20It%20is%20enjoyed%20for%20lunch%20and%20dinner%20with%20a%20bowl%20of%20steamed%20rice.%20It%20is%20said%20that%20the%20dish%20is%20a%20significant%20one%20in%20Assam%20and%20is%20a%20symbol%20of%20unity%20and%20togetherness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E6.%20Jholi%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fu39Nyx6ZXrE%3Fsi%3DPa4YNj0ytTckLTom%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20